node.title: SA records three new cases of COVID-19, three Qantas flights listed as exposure sites
node.alt: A line up of people with their luggage outside Adelaide Airport
node.description: South Australia recordsÂ three new cases of COVID-19, with three flights now listed as exposure locations.
node.content:
["South Australia has recorded three new cases of COVID-19, with three flights now listed as exposure locations.", "Today's cases are a man in his 50s and a woman in her 20s, who both acquired their infection interstate.", "The third case is a man in his 60s who acquired his infection overseas.", "SA Health said all cases are in isolation and have been transferred to a quarantine facility.", "Household close contacts are also in quarantine, SA Health said in a statement.", "SA Health announced new exposure locations this morning, including Qantas Flight 733 from Sydney to Adelaide, which arrived in the city at 10:15am Wednesday morning.", "The entire Qantas flight QF0739, which also arrived in Adelaide from Sydney\u00a0on Wednesday, is another exposure site.", "Rows 15 to 19 on Qantas flight QF679, which arrived in Adelaide from Melbourne on Tuesday, is the third exposure site.\u00a0", "SA Health this morning said unvaccinated people who\u00a0were on flight QF 733 in the first four rows must immediately quarantine for 14 days, get tested straight away and be retested on days six and 13.", "Vaccinated contacts must immediately get tested and quarantine for seven days, with a\u00a0requirement\u00a0to retest on days six and 14.", "The rest of that\u00a0flight has been listed as a casual contact exposure location.", "Adelaide Airport and Krispy Kreme were also listed as casual contact exposure locations.", "A shopping centre in Brighton was listed as a low-risk casual contact site.", "SA Health is yet to release details of the other two flights.", "Yesterday, South Australia recorded its first two cases of COVID-19 since the borders were opened to vaccinated travellers on November 23.", "They included a young\u00a0Victorian girl who travelled to the state\u00a0by road with her family, and a Victorian man who tested positive for COVID a month ago.", "The man was not believed to be infectious.", "The girl and her family have now returned interstate to their home near the Victorian border to quarantine, while her two grandparents in SA will be required to undertake seven days of home quarantine.", "More to come.", "", "
What COVID-19 travel insurance doesn't cover you for(Emilia Terzon)
"]
